A vintage 1930s-style illustration depicting an enormous golden pyramid made of coins and paper currency slowly dissolving into sand, with tiny well-dressed figures in period attire standing at the base watching helplessly as the wealth crumbles and blows away into a vast empty desert landscape. The color palette features muted sepia tones, dusty golds, and faded blues, with dramatic Art Deco-inspired geometric shadows stretching across the barren ground. The sky shows a setting sun casting long melancholic rays through clouds of dissolving currency particles, creating an atmosphere of grand decline and economic erosion.
